history.content:
Don't take math54 after 16a if you did reasonably well. 16B is designed to build on it and strengthen you further for 70 and beyond. Besides, if you have any interest in ML, you really should be taking 16B. (There's a reason the DS major likes it if you take 16ab)

Remember, the lower division is designed to be doable if you work hard and smartly --- correcting bad form and learning how to study and approach the material properly. If you find yourself having to spend inordinate time (say > 20hr per week) you need to talk to your TAs and the Prof to figure out how to approach the material better. All of these courses are designed to be supportive of people taking them in the right order. 

Finding 16A more challenging than 61a is not unusual. Don't think anything of it.

children.subject: Is the 20hr per week including all sections and lec?

history.content: Hi, sophomore here. I took EE 16A last semester with 61A and did well in the course despite finding the workload at times to be heavy (even more than 61A) and struggling through some of the homework and labs. This semester, I decided to enroll in 61B and Math 54 in order to reduce my overall workload and to at least declare Data Science by the end of the year if all else fails, but I'm finding the content to be a bit redundant from what I've already learned. I would like to take EE 16B but I'm worried about getting a good grade in 61B first and I know that the projects can get very heavy for both classes, so I'm not really sure if I should just stick with Math 54 or go with EE 16B. Any advice on the workload of the class and which course would be better to take in this situation?
history.subject: Math 54 vs EE 16B
